This paper is about unsupervised neural machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a learning to route method, which involves training a neural network to make decisions, suggesting that it could also fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of neural networks for unsupervised translation also suggests that it could be relevant to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of image captioning datasets for evaluation, indicating that it could be related to cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper uses BLEU scores as a metric, which is commonly used in NLP and machine translation, suggesting that it could also be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
